The article announces several nominations and appointments made by the United States government. Colonel Douglas Macgregor has been nominated to be the Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Federal Republic of Germany. He is a decorated combat veteran and an expert on force design and grand strategy. Mark C. Christie has been nominated to be a Member of the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission. He is currently the Chairman of the Virginia State Corporation Commission and has extensive experience in state utility regulation. Allison Clements has also been nominated to be a Member of the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission. She has over two decades of experience in Federal energy regulation and is the founder and president of an energy policy and strategy consulting firm. Colonel Craig Duehring has been nominated to be the Deputy Under Secretary of Defense for Personnel and Readiness. He has served in various leadership roles in the Department of Defense and is a retired Air Force veteran. Lastly, Jon Harrison and Michael Newton have been nominated to be Members of the Arctic Research Commission.